ass="_ _a"></span>“我”<span class="_ _4"></span>？头发剃了，<span class="_ _a"></span>指甲剪了，<span class="_ _4"></span>是不是<span class="_ _a"></span>“我”<span class="_ _a"></span>就没有了？</div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 y3c ffb fs3 fc0 sc0 ls12 ws0">如果认为整个身体是“我”<span class="_ _6"></span><span class="ls13">，那么身体缺了一部分，比如一</span></div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 y3d ffb fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">只手没有了，是不是“我”就不完整了呢？ </div><div class="t m0 x22 h4 yb5 ffb fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">当然，<span class="_ _5"></span>这是佛教中特别细致的观察方法。<span class="_ _5"></span>虽然刚刚接触</div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 yb6 ffb fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">这些道理时，<span class="_ _5"></span>你不一定能马上接受并打破我执，<span class="_ _5"></span>但只要去深</div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 yb7 ffb fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">入学习，就会发现里面蕴含了甚深的智慧。通过这种智慧，</div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 y41 ffb fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">能打破我们的很多颠倒妄执。 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.500000,0.000000,0.000000,1.500000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
